### Required prerequisites

* Make sure you've read the [documentation](https://pybind11.readthedocs.io). Your issue may be addressed there.
* Search the [issue tracker](https://github.com/pybind/pybind11/issues) and [Discussions](https:/pybind/pybind11/discussions) to verify that this hasn't already been reported. +1 or comment there if it has.
* Consider asking first in the [Gitter chat room](https://gitter.im/pybind/Lobby) or in a [Discussion](https:/pybind/pybind11/discussions/new).

### Problem description

I'm using ArchLinux, an Intel processor, pybind11 version 2.6.1 and python version 3.9.7.

I want to generate a square matrix (vector<vector>) with a certain algorithm and use this matrix in python. However, when the square matrix has dimensions greater than 6x6, I get segmentation faults or double free error at the return statement.

```
$ python -c "import pybind_crash; pybind_crash.generate_matrix(10)"
finished generating
double free or corruption (out)
[1]    247496 abort (core dumped)  python -c "import pybind_crash; pybind_crash.generate_matrix(10)"
```

### Reproducible example code

```
#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>
#include <pybind11/stl.h>
#include <vector>


typedef std::vector<std::vector<int>> Matrix;

Matrix generateMatrix(int size) {
    Matrix matrix(size, std::vector<int>{size, 0});

    for (size_t i=0; i<size; i++)
        for (size_t j=i+1; j<size; j++)
            matrix[i][j] = 1;
    printf("finished generating\n");

    return matrix;
}

PYBIND11_MODULE(pybind_crash, m) {
    m.def("generate_matrix", &generateMatrix);
}
```
